Okay after a little more digging I realized the problem is that by creating an `__init__` method in my `MainAccounts` I Overridden the parent class `Resource`'s `__init__` method. So in order to fix this i just invoked super like so:

```python
@api.route('/api/mcc/main')
class MainAccounts(Resource):

    def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
        self.__client = get_client('main-mcc')
        super().__init__(api, *args, **kwargs) # python 3 style of invoking parent methods

    @marshal_with(account_model)
    @api.response(200, 'Success', account_model)
    def get(self) -> List[Dict]:
        return AccountModel(self.__client).get_mcc_accounts()
```

