> Make our code and especially our state transitions aware of chain reorganizations

Note: The idea is to not add logic for reorgs inside every task, but to have a top-level state-transition function, e.g.:

```python
class BlockchainConfirmation(State):
  def __init__(self, child_state):
     self.child_state = child_state
     self.ordered_events = []

def state_transition(new_state, state_change):
  # queue blockchain events until they reach the # of confirmations block required
  if isinstance(state_change, BlockChainEvent):
    self.ordered_events.append(state_change) 
  if isinstance(state_change, Block):
    i = 0
    for blockchain_event in self.ordered_events:
      if blockchain_event.blocknumber + CONFIRMATIONS_BLOCKS <= state_change.block_number:
         dispatch(self.child_state, blockchain_event)
         i += 1
    blockchain_event.blocknumber = blockchain_event.blocknumber[i:]
  ...
```

